para_trans: Setting up of Rural Hospital under Reservation at Gondia-Certificate
Government Sanitation Card No: - GRAUBA 2007 / P.No.367 / Health-3
10th Floor, Gokuldas Tejpal Hospital Complex Building,
Read: - 1) Government Decision, Public Health Department No: - GRAUBA 2007 / Q. No.367 / Health-3, D. Government Corrigendum dated 04.06.2008: -

Under the above-mentioned Government Decision, Soudand, Dt. Subject to conditions, approval has been accorded for setting up of a rural hospital under the Scheduled Castes at Sadak Arjuni G. Gondia. In this Government Decision, Clause No. 2 is as follows.

"(2) Recurring non-recurring expenditure on staff salaries for the proposed rural hospital is being approved for a period of one year from the funds under the balance within the limits prescribed by the balance committee. The expenditure incurred for this purpose should be covered under the following section.
(01) (07) - The Maharashtra Zilla Parishad and Panchayat Samiti Act, 1961
Grants for Schemes under Section 187 of the Act (2210 3065)
Instead, the. In the Government Judgment dated 04.06.2008, Clause No. 2 should read as follows.
"(2) The expenditure incurred on payment of salaries and allowances to the staff of the proposed rural hospitals shall be met from the grants sanctioned under the headings below.
(01) (08) - Upgradation of Primary Health Centre to the level of Rural Hospital, (2210 0413) "
Government Sanitation Card No: - GRAUBA 2007 / P.No.367 / Health-3
The Government Corrigendum is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
